Sentencas: In an attempt to optimize the properties of FeCoNi coating for planar solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) interconnect application, the coating composition is modified by increasing the ratio of Fe/Ni.
Titulo: Sputtered Fe1•5CoNi0.5 coating: An improved protective coating for SOFC interconnect applications

Sentencas: An Fe1.5CoNi0.5 (Fe:Co:Ni = 1.5:1:0.5, atomic ratio) metallic coating is fabricated on SUS 430 stainless steel by magnetron sputtering, followed by oxidation in air at 800 degrees C. The Fe1.5CoNi0.5 coating is thermally converted to (Fe,Co,Ni)(3)O-4 and (Fe,Co,Mn,Ni)(3)O-4 without (Ni,Co)O particles.
Titulo: Sputtered Fe1•5CoNi0.5 coating: An improved protective coating for SOFC interconnect applications

Sentencas: After oxidation for 1680 h, no further migration of Cr is detected in the thermally converted coating region.
Titulo: Sputtered Fe1•5CoNi0.5 coating: An improved protective coating for SOFC interconnect applications

Sentencas: A low oxidation rate of 5.9 x 10(-14) g(2) cm(-4) s(-1) and area specific resistance of 12.64 m Omega center dot cm(2) is obtained for Fe1.5CoNi0.5 coated steels.
Titulo: Sputtered Fe1•5CoNi0.5 coating: An improved protective coating for SOFC interconnect applications
